    "Figure 5 shows the visibility amplitude versus (u, v) distance for 2018 April 21 and 25, overlaid on 2017 April 11.",
    "The a prioriand network-calibrated visibility amplitudes (see M 87 * 2017 III, for details) display the characteristic secondary peak beyond",
    "A79, page 8 of 63 The Event Horizon Telescope Collaboration: A&A, 681, A79 (2024) 15 16 17 18 19 20 21 -80 -60 -40 -20 Closure Phase (deg) ALMA-LMT-SMT 15 16 17 18 19 20 21 -200 -100 0 100 200 JCMT-LMT-SMT 15 16 17 18 19 20 21 GMST (h) 0 100 Closure Phase (deg) ALMA-LMT-SMA 15 16 17 18 19 20 21 GMST (h) -50 0 ALMA-GLT-LMT 2017 April 06 2017 April 11 2018 April 21 a deep amplitude minima at ∼3.4 Gλ, also observed in 2017 (M 87 * 2017 IV), despite the differences in the (u, v) coverage.",
    "A ring-like structure will also produce a second null beyond ∼8.3 Gλ.",
    "However, the longest baseline the EHT can probe is 8 Gλ between the Hawai'i and PV stations, which has only one detection on 2018 April 25."
